<paragraph blockId="4.[136,1452,1929,2066]" lastBlockId="5.[136,1452,158,617]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="158" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,443,2037,2063]" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">Conservation Status:</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[443,723,2037,2063]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="157">
— 
<taxonomicName box="[472,723,2037,2063]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alternifolia">Bertolonia alternifolia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has an EOO of 
<quantity box="[916,1024,2038,2066]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.193" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" unit="km" value="4.193">4.193 km</quantity>
² and AOO of 
<quantity box="[1193,1304,2038,2066]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.402" pageId="4" pageNumber="157" unit="km" value="1.402">1.402 km</quantity>
², and should be classified as “Critically Endangered” (CR), following 
<bibRefCitation author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[780,930,158,184]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" refId="ref19879" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Subcommittee (2017) Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 13 (March 2017). Prepared by the IUCN species survival commission. IUCN Council, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK, 108 pp. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedList Guidelines. pdf (Accessed 9 February 2019)" type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
categories. This species has been found in the “Serra do Peito de Moça” inside the “Parque Nacional Serra das Lontras” and in areas bordering the park.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[136,1452,158,617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,230,256]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName box="[294,549,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alternifolia">
<emphasis box="[294,549,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Bertolonia alternifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to 
<collectingRegion box="[725,793,230,256]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, occurring in montane rainforests and cloud forests (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[341,1239,654,1912]" captionTargetId="figure-255@5.[340,1247,641,1924]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A. Bertolonia alternifolia. B. Bertolonia angustipetala. C. Bertolonia bullata. D. Bertolonia carmoi. E. Bertolonia cuspidata. F. Bertolonia hirsutissima. G. Bertolonia igrapiuna. H. Bertolonia kollmannii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597686" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597686/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Fig. 3a</figureCitation>
). Collected with flowers from September to April and fruits from September to May. 
<taxonomicName box="[1167,1423,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alternifolia">
<emphasis box="[1167,1423,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Bertolonia alternifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the branches, petioles, leaf blades, hypanthium, and sepals densely glandulose-villose (trichomes 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="2.0">2–4 mm</quantity>
long), alternate leaves, blades 3.4–7.3 × 
<quantity box="[642,771,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.8" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="cm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.8" valueMin="2.2">2.2–5.8 cm</quantity>
, flowers with long petals (
<quantity box="[1069,1191,338,365]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.45" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="14.5" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="11.0">11–18 mm</quantity>
) and long anthers (
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5 mm</quantity>
) with extrorse pores. Along with 
<taxonomicName box="[555,834,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="angustipetala">
<emphasis box="[555,834,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Bertolonia angustipetala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[848,1005,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">
<taxonomicName box="[848,1002,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kollmannii">B. kollmannii</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[1059,1451,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">
<taxonomicName box="[1059,1188,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="violacea">B. violacea</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1199,1451,374,400]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alternifolia">Bertolonia alternifolia</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has the smallest leaves in the genus (
<quantity box="[553,680,410,437]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.9" metricValueMax="7.3" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="cm" value="4.9" valueMax="7.3" valueMin="2.5">2.5–7.3 cm</quantity>
long). A recently published species from the state of 
<collectingRegion box="[1284,1448,410,436]" country="Brazil" name="Espirito Santo" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Espírito Santo</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Bacci &amp; R. Goldenberg" authorityName="Bacci &amp; R. Goldenberg" box="[136,722,446,473]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="michelangeliana">
<emphasis box="[136,450,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">Bertolonia michelangeliana</emphasis>
Bacci &amp; R. Goldenberg
</taxonomicName>
(in 
<bibRefCitation author="Bacci, L. F. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Goldenberg, R." box="[767,1030,446,473]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" pagination="1663 - 1676" refId="ref18480" refString="Bacci, L. F., Amorim, A. M. &amp; Goldenberg, R. (2017) Flora do Espirito Santo: Bertolonia (Melastomataceae). Rodriguesia 68 (5): 1663 - 1676. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / 2175 - 7860201768510" type="journal article" year="2017">
Bacci 
<emphasis box="[838,888,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">et al</emphasis>
. 2017: 1670
</bibRefCitation>
) also has alternate leaves and anthers with extrorse pores. They differ by the shorter petioles (
<quantity box="[760,886,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.5" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.5" valueMin="1.5">1.5–5.5 cm</quantity>
long) in 
<taxonomicName box="[988,1145,482,508]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alternifolia">
<emphasis box="[988,1145,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">B. alternifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[1162,1185,483,508]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">vs</emphasis>
. longer, 
<quantity box="[1283,1422,482,509]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.4" metricValueMax="13.6" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="cm" value="8.4" valueMax="13.6" valueMin="3.2">3.2–13.6 cm</quantity>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[136,354,518,544]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="michelangeliana">
<emphasis box="[136,354,518,544]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">B. michelangeliana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), leaves with 3–5 main veins (v 
<emphasis box="[708,719,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">s</emphasis>
. 7–9 main veins), flowers with only glandulose-punctate pedicels and bigger petals, with 11–18 × 
<quantity box="[493,620,554,581]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="10.5" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="8.75" valueMax="10.5" valueMin="7.0">7–10.5 mm</quantity>
(
<emphasis box="[635,658,555,580]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">vs</emphasis>
. flowers with glandulose-punctate and also glandulose-villose pedicels and smaller petals, with 10–13 × 
<quantity box="[509,627,590,617]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.6" metricValueMax="7.2" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" unit="mm" value="6.6" valueMax="7.2" valueMin="6.0">6–7.2 mm</quantity>
). For more details, see 
<bibRefCitation author="Baumgratz, J. F. A. &amp; Amorim, A. M. &amp; Jardim, A. B." box="[886,1152,590,617]" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" pagination="273 - 279" refId="ref18825" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A., Amorim, A. M. &amp; Jardim, A. B. (2011) Two new species of Bertolonia (Melastomataceae) from the Brazilian Atlantic Forest. Kew Bulletin 66: 273 - 279. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 12225 - 011 - 9281 - 0" type="journal article" year="2011">
Baumgratz 
<emphasis box="[1016,1065,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="158">et al</emphasis>
. (2011)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation box="[1206,1290,590,616]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2" pageId="5" pageNumber="158" tableUuid="DF76660492567734FF76FDBFF843BEC2">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
